

The numbers are placed in an anticlockwise square spiral beginning  

\[
\begin{matrix}
5&4&3\\[2pt]
6&1&2\\[2pt]
7&8&9
\end{matrix}
\]

so that  

* 1 is at \((0,0)\);
* the right‑hand neighbour of a number is reached by increasing the \(x\)‑coordinate,
* the up‑hand neighbour by increasing the \(y\)‑coordinate.

---

### 1.  Locate 2026 in the spiral  

Let  

\[
r=\left\lceil\frac{\sqrt{2026}-1}{2}\right\rceil .
\]

Since \(\sqrt{2026}\approx45.01\),

\[
r=23 .
\]

The outer side of ring \(r\) has length \(2r+1=47\) and its maximal number is \((2r+1)^2=47^2=2209\).  
The previous ring ends at \((2r-1)^2=45^2=2025\).

Thus

\[
2026=(2r-1)^2+1
\]

is the *first* number of ring 23. Its coordinates are the start point of the ring,

\[
(x,y)=(r,\,-(r-1))=(23,-22).
\]

---

### 2.  Coordinates of the eight neighbours  

\[
\begin{array}{c|c}
\text{coordinate} & \text{ring}\\\hline
(22,-23) & r=23\\
(22,-22) & r=22\\
(22,-21) & r=22\\
(23,-23) & r=23\\
(23,-21) & r=23\\
(24,-23) & r=24\\
(24,-22) & r=24\\
(24,-21) & r=24
\end{array}
\]

---

### 3.  Numbers at those coordinates  

For a ring \(R\) we use  

* start of the ring:   \(\displaystyle n_{\!s}= (2R-1)^2+1\);
* top‑right corner:   \(n_{TR}= (2R-1)^2+2R\);
* top‑left corner:    \(n_{TL}= (2R-1)^2+4R\);
* bottom‑left corner: \(n_{BL}= (2R-1)^2+6R\);
* bottom‑right corner:\(n_{BR}= (2R+1)^2\).

On a side the numbers increase by one per step.

Applying this:

| coordinate | number |
|------------|--------|
| (22,-23) | \(n_{BL}^{(23)}+(22+23)=2163+45=2208\) |
| (22,-22) | bottom‑right corner of ring 22: \(45^2=2025\) |
| (22,-21) | start of ring 22: \(1849+1=1850\) |
| (23,-23) | bottom‑right corner of ring 23: \(47^2=2209\) |
| (23,-21) | one step up from start of ring 23: \(2026+1=2027\) |
| (24,-23) | start of ring 24: \(2209+1=2210\) |
| (24,-22) | one step up from start of ring 24: \(2210+1=2211\) |
| (24,-21) | two steps up from start of ring 24: \(2210+2=2212\) |

---

### 4.  Sum of the eight neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
S&=2208+2025+1850+2209+2027+2210+2211+2212\\
&=16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

---

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
----
